# Copy to `.dev.vars` for local `wrangler pages dev`. NEVER commit `.dev.vars`.
# In production this value is a Pages *secret* (Settings → Environment variables
# → encrypted) named SESSION_SECRET — set by the user, never by code.
#
# Generate a strong value, e.g.:  openssl rand -hex 32
SESSION_SECRET="dev-only-insecure-secret-change-me-0000000000000000"

# (Optional) Email verification + password reset via Resend (https://resend.com).
# Leave BOTH unset to run without email — signup/login still work and the
# email-only features are disabled with an in-app notice. Never commit real keys.
#   RESEND_API_KEY="re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
#   EMAIL_FROM="WIE <noreply@yourdomain>"
